Let $p=p(n)$ be a sequence of densities, i.e., $0\leq p\leq 1 $, and let $\beta=\beta(n)$.
An $n$-vertex graph $\Gamma$ is called $(p,\beta)$-\emph{jumbled} if 
\begin{equation*}
\left|e_{\Gamma}(X,Y)-p\vol(X,Y)\right| \leq \beta \vol(X,Y)^{1/2},
\end{equation*}
for all $X,Y \subseteq V(\Gamma).$

\label{ranksOfReductions}
