  is an exact sequence, where $\iota$ denotes the inclusion $(A,\es)\to (X,\es)$ and $\pi$ denotes the inclusion $(X,\es)\to (X,A)$. These boundary homomorphisms are \emph{natural}, i.e.\ given a standard map $f:(X,A)\to(Y,B)$ the diagrams
