Let $M$ be a mixed graph with vertex set $V(M)=\{v_{1},v_{2},\ldots,v_{n}\}$ and $d_{k}$ is the degree of $v_{k}$, $k=1,2,\ldots,n$. Let $H(M)$ and $R_{H}(M)$ be the Hermitian-adjacency matrix and Hermitian-Randi\'{c} matrix of $M$, respectively. If $M$ has isolated vertices, then $\emph{det}H(M)=\emph{det}R_{H}(M)=0$. If $M$ has no isolated vertices, then
