Let $M$ be a mixed graph of order $n$ and $\mu_{1}\geq\mu_{2}\geq\cdots\geq\mu_{n}$ be the Hermitian-Randi\'{c} spectrum of $R_{H}(M)$. Let $M_{U}$ be the underlying graph of $M$, $p=|\emph{det}R_{H}(M)|$. Then $$\sqrt{2R_{-1}(M_{U})+n(n-1)p^{\frac{2}{n}}}\leq\mathcal{E}_{R_{H}}(M)\leq\sqrt{2nR_{-1}(M_{U})},$$
